  Library preparation preflight produced setup context.
  
  Summary: Apache Pulsar Java client is primarily exercised through producer/consumer/reader operations against a running Pulsar broker; the artifact is otherwise self-contained, but meaningful end-to-end coverage needs a standalone broker.
  
  Already applied by Forge:
  - Use Docker image apachepulsar/pulsar:4.2.1 (allow-list slug pulsar) (applied)
  
  Agent guidance:
  Start a standalone broker with command `bin/pulsar standalone`, expose broker port `6650` and HTTP/admin port `8080`, wait for readiness before creating the client, and build clients with `PulsarClient.builder().serviceUrl("pulsar://<host>:<mapped-6650>").build()`. Use unique topic names under `persistent://public/default/` and close producers, consumers, readers, and clients to avoid thread/resource leaks.
  
  Setup to perform in the generated work:
